msgctxt "mn78:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 78 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 78 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn78:0.2"
msgid "Samaṇamuṇḍikasutta "
msgstr "With Uggāhamāna Samaṇamuṇḍika "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli2.23, sc1
msgctxt "mn78:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn78:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Comm has “row” for cīra, which seems like a stretch. I can’t find it attested elsewhere in this sense. Skt dict acknowledges the sense row, line, but only in late sources, and I don’t know if it is relevant. BB renders it as “plantation”, evidently referring to the rows of trees in a plantation, though from the commentary’s description it sounds more like a decorative row or hedge. Normally it refers to strips of bark or cloth. At MN 12 we have the simile of a tindukakhanu (ebony trunk) flaking off bark (papatika). And at DN 24 we have the tindukakhāṇu-paribbājakārāmo. I suspect the usual meaning of cīra should apply, i.e. “park littered with strips of tinduka bark”, or perhaps even “the single hall, lined with strips of tinduka bark”. I am at a loss to explain the long ā in sandhi. In DN 24, perhaps also we might read “monastery built from tinduka stumps”. But tinduka is not usually used as a building material, nor is an arama a building. Regarding the numbers, the variants are 300 and 500, I have chosen the less common number.
msgctxt "mn78:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto samayappavādake tindukācīre ekasālake mallikāya ārāme paṭivasati mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ pañcamattehi paribbājakasatehi. "
msgstr "Now at that time the wanderer Uggāhamāna Samaṇamuṇḍikāputta was residing together with around three hundred wanderers in Mallikā’s single-halled monastery for group debates, set among the flaking pale-moon ebony trees. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn78:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati sāvatthiyā nikkhami divā divassa bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "Then the master builder Pañcakaṅga left Sāvatthī in the middle of the day to see the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn78:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho pañcakaṅgassa thapatissa etadahosi: "
msgstr "It occurred to him, "

msgctxt "mn78:2.3"
msgid "“akālo kho tāva bhagavantaṃ dassanāya; "
msgstr "“It’s the wrong time to see the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn78:2.4"
msgid "paṭisallīno bhagavā. "
msgstr "as he’s in retreat. "

msgctxt "mn78:2.5"
msgid "Manobhāvaniyānampi bhikkhūnaṃ asamayo dassanāya; "
msgstr "And it’s the wrong time to see the esteemed mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn78:2.6"
msgid "paṭisallīnā manobhāvaniyā bhikkhū. "
msgstr "as they’re in retreat. "

msgctxt "mn78:2.7"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena samayappavādako tindukācīro ekasālako mallikāya ārāmo yena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go to Mallikā’s monastery to visit the wanderer Uggāhamāna?” "

msgctxt "mn78:2.8"
msgid "Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yena samayappavādako tindukācīro ekasālako mallikāya ārāmo yena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "So that’s what he did. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn78:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ nisinno hoti unnādiniyā uccāsaddamahāsaddāya anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentiyā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "Now at that time, Uggāhamāna was sitting together with a large assembly of wanderers making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as "

msgctxt "mn78:3.2"
msgid "rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā. "
msgstr "talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "mn78:3.3"
msgid "Addasā kho uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "Uggāhamāna saw Pañcakaṅga coming off in the distance, "

msgctxt "mn78:3.4"
msgid "Disvāna sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhāpesi: "
msgstr "and hushed his own assembly, "

msgctxt "mn78:3.5"
msgid "“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha; "
msgstr "“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound. "

msgctxt "mn78:3.6"
msgid "ayaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako āgacchati pañcakaṅgo thapati. "
msgstr "Here comes Pañcakaṅga, a disciple of the ascetic Gotama. "

msgctxt "mn78:3.7"
msgid "Yāvatā kho pana samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakā gihī odātavasanā sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti ayaṃ tesaṃ aññataro pañcakaṅgo thapati. "
msgstr "He is included among the white-clothed lay disciples of the ascetic Gotama, who is residing in Sāvatthī. "

msgctxt "mn78:3.8"
msgid "Appasaddakāmā kho pana te āyasmanto appasaddavinītā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādino; "
msgstr "Such venerables like the quiet, are educated to be quiet, and praise the quiet. "

msgctxt "mn78:3.9"
msgid "appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.” "

msgctxt "mn78:3.10"
msgid "Atha kho te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then those wanderers fell silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli2.24, sc4
msgctxt "mn78:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā uggāhamānena paribbājakena samaṇamuṇḍikāputtena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then Pañcakaṅga approached Uggāhamāna, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn78:4.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. Uggāhamāna said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5
msgctxt "mn78:5.1"
msgid "“catūhi kho ahaṃ, gahapati, dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ. "
msgstr "“Householder, when an individual has four qualities I describe them as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment. "

msgctxt "mn78:5.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "mn78:5.3"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, na kāyena pāpakammaṃ karoti, na pāpakaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati, na pāpakaṃ saṅkappaṃ saṅkappeti, na pāpakaṃ ājīvaṃ ājīvati—"
msgstr "It’s when they do no bad deeds with their body; speak no bad words; think no bad thoughts; and don’t earn a living by bad livelihood. "

msgctxt "mn78:5.4"
msgid "imehi kho ahaṃ, gahapati, catūhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhan”ti. "
msgstr "When an individual has these four qualities I describe them as an invincible ascetic.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc5
msgctxt "mn78:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati uggāhamānassa paribbājakassa samaṇamuṇḍikāputtassa bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandi nappaṭikkosi. "
msgstr "Then Pañcakaṅga neither approved nor dismissed that mendicant’s statement. "

msgctxt "mn78:6.2"
msgid "Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi: "
msgstr "He got up from his seat, thinking, "

msgctxt "mn78:6.3"
msgid "“bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I will learn the meaning of this statement from the Buddha himself.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7
msgctxt "mn78:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "mn78:7.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yāvatako ahosi uggāhamānena paribbājakena samaṇamuṇḍikāputtena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi. "
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all that had been discussed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli2.25, sc6
msgctxt "mn78:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "mn78:8.2"
msgid "“evaṃ sante kho, thapati, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako sampannakusalo bhavissati paramakusalo uttamapattipatto samaṇo ayojjho, yathā uggāhamānassa paribbājakassa samaṇamuṇḍikāputtassa vacanaṃ. "
msgstr "“Master builder, if what Uggāhamāna says is true, a little baby boy is an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment. "

msgctxt "mn78:8.3"
msgid "Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa kāyotipi na hoti, kuto pana kāyena pāpakammaṃ karissati, aññatra phanditamattā. "
msgstr "For a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘a body’, so how could they possibly do a bad deed with their body, apart from just wriggling? "

msgctxt "mn78:8.4"
msgid "Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa vācātipi na hoti, kuto pana pāpakaṃ vācaṃ bhāsissati, aññatra roditamattā. "
msgstr "And a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘speech’, so how could they possibly speak bad words, apart from just crying? "

#. VAR: vikūjitamattā → vikuj­jatta­mattā (si) | vikujjitamattā (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn78:8.5"
msgid "Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa saṅkappotipi na hoti, kuto pana pāpakaṃ saṅkappaṃ saṅkappissati, aññatra vikūjitamattā. "
msgstr "And a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘thought’, so how could they possibly think bad thoughts, apart from just whimpering? "

msgctxt "mn78:8.6"
msgid "Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa ājīvotipi na hoti, kuto pana pāpakaṃ ājīvaṃ ājīvissati, aññatra mātuthaññā. "
msgstr "And a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘livelihood’, so how could they possibly earn a living by bad livelihood, apart from their mother’s breast? "

msgctxt "mn78:8.7"
msgid "Evaṃ sante kho, thapati, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako sampannakusalo bhavissati paramakusalo uttamapattipatto samaṇo ayojjho, yathā uggāhamānassa paribbājakassa samaṇamuṇḍikāputtassa vacanaṃ. "
msgstr "If what Uggāhamāna says is true, a little baby boy is an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "mn78:8.8"
msgid "Catūhi kho ahaṃ, thapati, dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi na ceva sampannakusalaṃ na paramakusalaṃ na uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ, api cimaṃ daharaṃ kumāraṃ mandaṃ uttānaseyyakaṃ samadhigayha tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "When an individual has four qualities I describe them, not as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment—but as having achieved the same level as a little baby. "

msgctxt "mn78:8.9"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "mn78:8.10"
msgid "Idha, thapati, na kāyena pāpakammaṃ karoti, na pāpakaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati, na pāpakaṃ saṅkappaṃ saṅkappeti, na pāpakaṃ ājīvaṃ ājīvati—"
msgstr "It’s when they do no bad deeds with their body; speak no bad words; think no bad thoughts; and don’t earn a living by bad livelihood. "

msgctxt "mn78:8.11"
msgid "imehi kho ahaṃ, thapati, catūhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi na ceva sampannakusalaṃ na paramakusalaṃ na uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ, api cimaṃ daharaṃ kumāraṃ mandaṃ uttānaseyyakaṃ samadhigayha tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "When an individual has these four qualities I describe them, not as an invincible ascetic, but as having achieved the same level as a little baby. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc8
msgctxt "mn78:9.1"
msgid "Dasahi kho ahaṃ, thapati, dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ. "
msgstr "When an individual has ten qualities, master builder, I describe them as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn78:9.2"
msgid "Ime akusalā sīlā; "
msgstr "But certain things must first be understood, I say. ‘These are unskillful behaviors.’ "

